DataElement.preferredName: Rhabdoid Tumor Characteristic Present Percentage Value
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the percentage of the rhabdoid features present in the patient's cancer.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: An aggressive malignant embryonal neoplasm usually occurring during childhood.  It is characterized by the presence of large cells with abundant cytoplasm, large eccentric nucleus, and a prominent nucleolus and it is associated with abnormalities of chromosome 22.  It can arise from the central nervous system, kidney, and the soft tissues.  The prognosis is poor._The distinguishing qualities or prominent aspect of a person, object, action, process, or substance._Being or existing in a specified place or at the specified time.
